==English==
===Phrase===
'''[[on]] [[the]] [[wagon]]'''
# {{idiom}} [[abstain|Abstaining]] from [[drink]]ing any [[alcoholic]] drink, usually in the sense of having given it up (as opposed to never having partaken).
#: 1917: ''"Thank you, but; &ndash; er &ndash; I'm on the wagon, you know," declined the youth.'' &mdash; [[w:Edgar Rice Burroughs|Edgar Rice Burroughs]], ''The Oakdale Affair'' [http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/363]
# By extension, [[maintaining]] a [[program]] of self-[[improvement]] or [[abstinence]] from some other undesirable [[habit]].
#:''He's been '''on the''' smoking cessation '''wagon''' for two weeks now.''

===Antonyms===
*[[off the wagon]]